In a message dated 8/19/2002 8:43:50 AM Pacific Daylight Time, 
Apillow(-at-)manh.com writes:
> The Bentley has these very nice pullers shown in the book... But of course 
> those are not available to normal folks.  So what do you all use to pull 
> out the ball bearings?  

Hi Adrian,
For small nut trannies in a pinch one can put a 17mm Allen wrench in the RGB 
fill/drain plugs and hammer sideways on this wrench to bump the RGB half and 
lower outer bearing off.
Eric&Barb

